BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:PZxDDsAP64NNGcolkVFO2
SUMMARY:Fix-it Fair
DTSTAMP:20260307T213057Z
DTSTART:20260307T130000Z
DESCRIPTION:Bring your broken items to the Fix-it Fair. The PNA Fixers will
	 diagnose and repair your item for free (parts may be extra) while also he
	lping reduce waste in Seattle. At the same time\\\, you can bond with the 
	rest of your local community and learn something new by watching the repai
	r. Typical items include heaters\\\, sewing machines\\\, waffle irons\\\, 
	blenders\\\, mixers\\\, electric bikes\\\, extension cords\\\, lamps\\\, a
	udio gear\\\, and more. There are hardware stores nearby if you need to fe
	tch parts. There is also a professional knife sharpener on hand\\\, and we
	 expect to have sewists to mend and hem clothing. Walk-ins are welcome but
	 it’s helpful if you can RSVP to let us know what you’re bringing: bit.ly/
	GreenwoodFix-itFair. The PNA Fixers meet regularly at Greenwood Hardware o
	n the first Wednesday of every month\\\, 3–6 pm. \\nFree\\\, but donations
	 are appreciated. \\n\n\nhttps://www.phinneycenter.org/event/fix-it-fair/\
	n\nFrom Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/fix-it-fair/
LOCATION:Greenwood Senior Center\\\, 525 N. 85th St.\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\,
	 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
