BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:iR6h6vAt1g5zILrfq1lqr
SUMMARY:Ballard Bookworms Community Storytime
DTSTAMP:20260307T213057Z
DTSTART:20260322T103000Z
DESCRIPTION:Calling all bookworms! Ballard Preschool Co-op (BPC) is thrille
	d to present its FREE monthly Ballard Bookworms story time. Join BPC’s bel
	oved Teacher Christine for a fun and engaging story time designed to spark
	 a love of reading and build connections within our community. \\nThis mon
	th our Special Guest is Emily Weissman (known online as Urb.Em.Sketches) a
	 local urban sketcher\\\, author and illustrator. Emily’s watercolor paint
	ings celebrate beloved neighborhood places that make Seattle extraordinary
	. She will be reading her children’s book\\\, My Home is With You\\\, a wh
	imsical exploration of how home is not just a place\\\, but found in the h
	earts of those we love. \\nBallard Bookworms is free and open to the publi
	c\\\, so be sure to invite your friends & neighbors! Recommended for ages 
	5 and under (older siblings welcome) \\nThis program is organized by the B
	allard Preschool Co-op and is held in a library branch meeting room. The S
	eattle Public Library does not sponsor or endorse this event.\n\nhttps://m
	yballard.com/event/ballard-bookworms-community-storytime/\n\nFrom My Balla
	rd
URL:https://myballard.com/event/ballard-bookworms-community-storytime/
LOCATION:Greenwood Public Library\\\, 8016 Greenwood Ave N\\\,\\\, Seattle\
	\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:myballard
CATEGORIES:My Ballard
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
